    &lt;Title&gt;Terrible. Should not be called rehab.&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Appaling  neuro 'rehab'. There is no equipment to use, physio only comes once or twice week for about 10 minutes. There is no engagement from staff who sit about chatting but totally ignore and do not engage with patients. Health and recovery is not promoted there are limited opportunities to develop or re learn any type of skills. There is limited awareness of mental health and patients are expected to sit and stare into space all day everyday. Still no access to a wheelchair. Not supported to use an actual toilet. Patients are written off and there is no/ exceptionally limited opportunity to make any kind of progress. This 'rehab' is truly terrible.                                   
                Staff need to actually engage with patients, promote their health and enable them opportunity to make progress. Get some equipment and services! This is not good enough and does not deserve the title 'rehab'.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
